parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can result in serious injuries or fatalities, as the occupants are not adequately protected.
symptoms: Airbags fail to deploy in the event of a crash
despite the severity of the impact
resulting in injuries or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning of the front seat belt retractors can cause the seat belts to jam or fail to extend properly, increasing the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belts do not retract or extend properly
the seat belts snag or catch in the guide ring
the seat belts become loose or difficult to secure
the seat belts require multiple attempts to fully extend or retract.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission stays in a specific gear
the transmission slips
the transmission lurches or sticks while driving
the check engine light comes on
error codes P0734 and P1624 appear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to lose power, making it difficult to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch is going out
the clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission hydraulic system can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Leaking fluid from the axle seal
missing locking clip on the right drive axle
transmission fluid leak.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: All electrical parts fail
transmission malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The emergency brake light illuminates
the rear tires lock up
the brakes "grab" when wet
the brake pedal feels spongy or soft.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various components to malfunction, leading to safety risks and inconvenience.
symptoms: The alarm system malfunctions
the radio stops working
the vehicle won't start
the check engine light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door latch can cause the door to stick or fall off, leading to safety risks and inconvenience.
symptoms: The door sticks or won't open
the door falls off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The buildup of carbon on the engine can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, leading to safety risks and inconvenience.
symptoms: The vehicle won't start
the engine stalls.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Spark Plug and Oxygen Sensor Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the spark plugs and oxygen sensor can cause the vehicle to run poorly, leading to safety risks and decreased performance.
symptoms: The vehicle has a hard time starting
the check engine light comes on.
